Wash and dry all produce. Bring 3/4 cup water and @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit} to a boil in a
#small pot{}. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP. Thinly slice
@Persian cucumber{1}. Zest @lemon{1} and @blood orange{1} until you have ½ tsp zest each.
Halve lemon. Peel blood orange, then thinly slice crosswise into rounds. Remove any seeds.

When water is boiling, add @couscous{1/2%cup} to small pot. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand until rest of meal is ready.

== Vinaigrette ==

In a #small bowl{}, whisk shallot, juice of one lemon half, ½ tsp lemon zest, ½ tsp
blood orange zest, @honey{1/2%ounce}, and 2 TBSP @olive oil{7%teaspoon} from bottle. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Salmon ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season
@skin-on salmon{12%ounce} all over with salt, pepper, and @Turkish spice blend{1%tablespoon}.
Add to pan skinside down. Cook until skin is crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Flip and cook on other
side to desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Salad ==

Toss @arugula{2%ounce}, blood orange rounds, @almonds{1%ounce}, cucumber, and half the
vinaigrette in a #large bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If salad needs more dressing, add a squeeze of lemon and a drizzle of olive oil and toss

== To Serve ==

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}, then drizzle with remaining vinaigrette. Divide couscous
between plates and top with salmon. Serve with salad on the side.